unemployment /ˌʌnɪmˈplɔɪmənt/

1. N-UNCOUNT Unemployment is the fact that people who want jobs cannot get them. 失业 

例： The state's unemployment rate rose slightly to 7.1 percent last month. 该国的失业率上个月略微上升到7.1%。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Unemployment is the same as . 失业救济金 [美国英语] 

例： He worked most of the year. Now he's getting unemployment. 他一年的大部分时间都在工作。现在他将得到失业救济金。

